The United States strongly condemns the recent terrorist attack in Kabul, Afghanistan, which resulted in the death of dozens of Afghan forces and civilians and the injury of hundreds more. The U.S. government expresses its condolences and solidarity with the victims and their families. Despite the ongoing violence, the U.S. remains committed to supporting the Afghan people and their government, urging the Taliban to seek peace instead of continuing their military campaign. The U.S. will continue to work alongside Afghan security forces to promote peace, stability, and counter the threat of terrorism in the region.